<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Up Vs. Yen, Down Vs. Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The dollar rose slightly against the Japanese  
yen, edging back from its lowest levels of the year. The dollar 
fell against the euro. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar was quoted at 109.11 Japanese yen in late New York  
trading, up from 109.05 late Wednesday. It last traded that low on 
Jan. 11, when it closed at 108.22 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar's meager gain against the yen came after a declining  
trend that had raised concerns that Japanese financial authorities 
might step into the market to push the dollar higher. An overly 
high yen could threaten Japan's struggling economy by making that 
country's exports less competitive. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0686, up from $1.0594 late Wednesday.  
</P>
<P>
	The dollar also was quoted at 1.4936 Swiss francs, down from  
1.5127, and 1.4952 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4896. The British 
pound rose to $1.6067 from $1.6062. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed rate. 
Based on Thursday's euro rate, the dollar was worth: 1.8301 German 
marks, down from 1.8453; 6.1379 French francs, down from 6.1889; 
and 1,812 Italian lire, down from 1,828. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
