<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Thursday, Sept. 2, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Lower; Dow Down 94.67  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks resumed their end-of-summer slump today  
as concerns about inflation and interest rates were compounded by a 
dismal earnings outlook from Sears, Roebuck and Co. The Dow Jones 
industrial average closed down 94.67 at 10,843.21, having worked 
its way back from a loss of 205 points earlier in the session. 
Broader stock indicators also closed lower. The Nasdaq composite 
index fell 16.17 to 2,734.63. Market fears escalated today as 
Federal Reserve Gov. Edward Kelley told Market News International 
it would be premature to assume the Fed will wait until next year 
to raise rates again. The Fed has already raised interest rates in 
June and August. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10843.21  - 94.67
NYSE Issues:         Advances  840  Declines 2084  Unchgd  581
