<DOCNO> APW19990902.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 19:50:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New Umpire Ejects Tampa Bay Manager </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- First-base umpire Marty Foster, who became a  
permanent member of the American League staff earlier in the day, 
ejected Tampa Bay manager Larry Rothschild in the sixth inning of 
Thursday night's game against Baltimore. 
</P>
<P>
	Rothschild protested Foster's safe call on Derrick May's  
grounder. Tampa Bay shortstop Aaron Ledesma fielded May's grounder 
and forced Albert Belle at second, but Foster ruled May beat second 
baseman Miguel Cairo's relay to avert an inning-ending double play. 
</P>
<P>
	Rothschild jogged to debate Foster's call behind first base.  
After a short, civil discussion, their argument became briefly 
animated before Foster ejected Rothschild. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the third ejection this season for Rothschild. Foster,  
39, had been a Triple-A umpire before Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was fine,'' Rothschild said. ``He gave me a chance to walk  
away.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
