<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Sears, Roebuck and Co., down 3 11/16 at 33 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The retailer expects third-quarter earnings to be between 63  
cents and 67 cents a share, well below analyst expectations of 82 
cents. Sears also announced a number of executive changes. 

</P>
<P>
 *Republic New York Corp., down 7 3/16 at 62 3/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Federal prosecutors and bank regulators are investigating  
whether Republic New York's securities unit inflated the value of 
assets of an investment fund, and provided inaccurate information 
to a major client. 

</P>
<P>
 *Talbots Inc., up 4 11/16 at 35 11/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Talbots said August same-store sales rose 18.1 percent. For the  
year to date, total sales for the retailer of classic women's 
clothing are up 11 percent to $669.3 million, and sales from stores 
open at least a year are up 6.8 percent. 

</P>
<P>
 *Labor Ready Inc., down 4 3/16 at 12    	
</P>
<P>
	Stephens Inc. trimmed its earnings expectations for the rest of  
1999, saying the sales force is too small following deep staff cuts 
made earlier in the year. Labor Ready is a temporary-employment 
agency focusing on light industrial and small business markets. 

</P>
<P>
 *Lone Star Industries Inc., up 14 9/16 at 49 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Lone Star, a maker of cement and ready-mixed concrete, will be  
acquired by Dyckerhoff AG for about $1.2 billion including assumed 
debt. Dyckerhoff is a German cement and building materials company. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Play-By-Play Toys &AMP; Novelties Inc., up 2 15/16 at 4 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company has been awarded licensing rights to the hugely  
popular Pokemon cartoon. Play-By-Play will make plush toys and 
novelties based on Pokemon for distribution to U.S. amusement 
parks. 

</P>
<P>
 *Com21 Inc., down 5 5/8 at 12 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company's cable modem failed to receive certification from  
Cable Television Laboratories Inc. A consortium run by CableLabs 
lets consumers know which cable modems comply with its 
specifications, often providing a boost in sales. 

</P>
<P>
 *Rambus Inc., down 4 3/4 at 90 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	Intel Corp. said it will begin using memory-chip technology made  
by Rambus's competitors. While Intel said it will continue using 
Rambus technology, it will also increase its use of less expensive 
alternatives. 

</P>
<P>
 *Regeneron Pharmaceuticals Inc., down 2 1/8 at 7 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Procter &AMP; Gamble Co. will return the rights to Regeneron's  
Axokine compound, which is being developed for the treatment of 
obesity and diabetes. Procter &AMP; Gamble dropped the rights after 
tests showed the compound is not suitable for all patients. 





  	   	
</P>
