<HEADLINE> Warriors Re-Sign Terry Cummings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- The Golden State Warriors re-signed  
veteran forward Terry Cummings to a multiyear contract on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial terms of the deal were not disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	The 38-year-old Cummings has averaged 16.6 points and 7.3  
rebounds over his 17-year NBA career, including 9.1 points and 5.1 
rebounds per game for the Warriors last season. 
</P>
<P>
	``His attitude and veteran leadership on the court and in the  
locker room proved invaluable last season and we expect the same 
this year,'' Warriors general manager Garry St. Jean said. ``I 
can't think of anyone better to aid in the development of our 
younger players.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Cummings was acquired from New York along with John Starks and  
Chris Mills, in exchange for Latrell Sprewell. 
  	   	
</P>
