<HEADLINE> Japan's Benchmark Stock Index Drops / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japan's benchmark stock index closed lower today as  
investors took profits from a sharp rise the previous day. The 
dollar inched higher against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average closed down 171.23  
points, or 0.96 percent, to 17,631.25. On Wednesday, the average 
finished 365.92 points, or 2.1 percent, higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 109.42 yen at late afternoon, up 0.20 yen from  
its level of 109.22 yen late Wednesday in Tokyo and also above its 
late New York level of 109.05 yen overnight. 
</P>
<P>
	In stock trading, traders said today's drop cloaked resilient  
market sentiment sustained by an overnight rebound on Wall Street 
and hopes for an economic recovery in Japan, analysts said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Despite the yen's strength, the market remains comparatively  
strong,'' said Kazunori Jinnai, deputy general manager at Daiwa 
Securities SB Capital Markets. 
</P>
<P>
	A strong yen makes Japanese exporters' products more expensive,  
and thus less competitive, overseas. Their foreign revenues also 
lose value in terms of the Japanese currency. 
</P>
<P>
	Retreating issues outnumbered advancers 871 to 372 on the Tokyo  
Stock Exchange's First Section, while 92 issues were unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
	In New York, the Dow Jones industrial average was up 108.60, or  
1 percent, to 10,937.88 at Wednesday's finish. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was up 0.75 points, or 0.05 percent, to 1,496.99. The 
TOPIX closed up 39.22 points, or 2.69 percent, the day before. 
</P>
<P>
	In foreign exchange dealings, the U.S. currency recovered some  
ground as U.S. and European hedge funds bought back oversold 
dollars, traders said. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar traded between 108.70 yen and 109.58 yen during Tokyo  
trading. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 115.86 yen in late  
afternoon, down from 116.08 yen late Wednesday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark No. 215 10-year Japanese government  
bond was unchanged from Wednesday's finish at 1.8800 percent. The 
price remained at 100.16 yen. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
