<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Storms continued over much of the East Coast today in the wake  
of Tropical Storm Dennis while storms also were expected to drench 
regions of the Gulf Coast and the Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	Areas of Maryland, Delaware, coastal Virginia and northeastern  
North Carolina could again expect winds up to 40 mph and heavy 
rains as Dennis was expected to linger off the East Coast for a few 
days. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, high pressure was expected to bring fair, dry  
conditions over other regions of the East. 
</P>
<P>
	Dry conditions also were forecast for the Ohio and Tennessee  
River Valleys, while showers and thunderstorms were expected over 
areas of the Gulf Coast, including Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama 
and the Florida panhandle. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers and thunderstorms over the northern Plains early today  
were expected to continue over parts of South Dakota, Nebraska, and 
Minnesota, while mostly sunny skies were forecast over the central 
and southern Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers also were forecast over parts of the Rockies including  
Wyoming, Utah, and Colorado, while monsoonal flow was expected to 
bring rain to areas of the Southwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Highs today were forecast in the 60s and 70s in parts of the  
northern Plains, northern Rockies and the Northwest; in the 80s in 
New England, the Ohio and Tennessee River Valleys and parts of the 
West Coast; and in the 90s in the Southeast, the central and 
southern Plains and the Southwest. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 on Wednesday ranged from 102  
degrees in Blythe, Calif., to 27 degrees in Meacham, Ore. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
