<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New Editor of Mademoiselle Named </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Mandi Norwood, 35, has been named editor of  
Mademoiselle, a Conde Nast magazine aimed at young women, the 
company announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Norwood had been editor of the British edition of Cosmopolitan,  
a post she held since July 1995. Cosmopolitan is owned by Conde 
Nast rival Hearst Magazines. 
</P>
<P>
	Elizabeth Crow stepped down from the post last week after six  
years as editor of the glossy magazine. Crow has agreed to stay on 
until December to see the magazine through the transition. 
</P>
<P>
	Conde Nast, which also publishes The New Yorker, Vanity Fair, GQ  
and Wired, is owned by the privately held Advance Publications Inc. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
