<HEADLINE> August, Year to Date Retail Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	August sales and sales for the fiscal year to date reported by  
leading retailers. 
</P>
<P>
	The sales compare the current year's sales with those of the  
previous year. Retailers are ranked according to results at the end 
of August. 
</P>
<P>
	Reporting periods vary slightly. Most retailers' fiscal years  
end in late January or early February. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales include those from stores open at least a year, also known  
as same-store or comparable store sales, and total sales. Retailers 
release only percentage changes for same-store sales, while they 
provide dollar figures and percentages for total sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Securities analysts and investors believe same-store sales  
provide a more accurate assessment of a retailer's performance than 
total sales. 

</P>
<P>
 *Wal-Mart Stores Inc.  
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended Aug. 27: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 8.7 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $13.03 billion, up 26.9 percent from $10.26  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Seven months ended Aug. 27: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 8.4 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $86.64 billion, up 16.9 percent from $74.14  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Sears, Roebuck and Co.	
</P>
<P>
 *Four weeks ended Aug. 28: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 0.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $2.93 billion, down 3.3 percent from $3.03  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Seven months ended Aug. 28: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $21.96 billion, down 3.2 percent from $22.68  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Kmart Corp.	
</P>
