<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-02 06:00:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lawton, Fan To Exchange Apologies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Minnesota Twins outfielder Matt Lawton will  
likely get off with an apology, and not be charged, after being 
caught on videotape spitting at a teen-age fan at the SkyDome. 
</P>
<P>
	It happened during the seventh inning of the Twins' 14-3 victory  
over Toronto on Tuesday night. Lawton, while running down a foul 
ball, was heckled by several fans. According to published reports, 
when a 16-year-old made a particularly insulting remark, Lawton 
spat towards him. 
</P>
<P>
	The fan then threw an empty cup at Lawton as the outfielder  
returned to his position. 
</P>
<P>
	``Your next paycheck is coming to me,'' the spectator yelled  
back at Lawton according to the Minneapolis Star-Tribune. 
</P>
<P>
	The incident was caught on videotape by TSN. The tape appears to  
show Lawton spitting toward the fan, but is inconclusive as to 
whether the fan was hit. The fan reportedly claims he was struck in 
the face. The tape also shows the fan made what appeared to be an 
obscene gesture to Lawton before the spitting incident. 
</P>
<P>
	A Toronto police spokesman said he received a call Wednesday  
night from the Twins telling him that they had settled the matter 
with the boy's family. 
</P>
<P>
	``When I do something wrong there's always punishment involved.  
I just want to make sure this doesn't happen again,'' Sgt. Peter 
Harmsen said the boy told him when he was deciding whether to press 
charges or not. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm satisfied there was an assault, but you need a complainant  
to go to court,'' Harmsen said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Star Tribune reported Lawton has been told by the Twins not  
to comment on the matter, but did say Wednesday that ``It takes a 
lot to make me snap.'' 
</P>
<P>
	When asked if the fan made a racial slur, Lawton, who is black,  
declined to comment. 
</P>
<P>
	``(Lawton) was taking a lot of abuse from the punks out there,''  
said a man sitting nearby. ``But it was nothing personal, it was 
just stuff like `you suck' when there was a fly ball.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
