<HEADLINE> Mets Have Altercation on Team Bus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- New York Mets shortstop Rey Ordonez needed six  
stitches over his left eye after a fight with fellow infielder Luis 
Lopez early Thursday morning on the team bus. 
</P>
<P>
	Ordonez is listed as day to day, general manager Steve Phillips  
said. Lopez, a reserve infielder, was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel confident that this is something that has been resolved  
on their basis and is behind us,'' Phillips said. ``This is one of 
those things that can happen when players are together over 162 
games.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The fight occurred about 4 a.m. EDT as the team bus was  
traveling from Newark Airport back to Shea Stadium. The Mets 
concluded a 3-3 road trip with a win at Houston on Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Ordonez, 26, was treated at the Hospital for Special Surgery.  
</P>
<P>
	Both players met separately and together Thursday with Phillips  
and senior assistant general manager Omar Minaya. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is something that seems to have been quickly resolved in a  
short afternoon meeting that I am confident is behind us,'' 
Phillips said. 
</P>
<P>
	The team would not disclose the nature of the fight or if either  
player was disciplined. 
  	   	
