<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 31 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 31  
points in today's early going. Losers on the New York Stock 
Exchange hold a 3-1 lead over gainers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is down 36 points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is down about five points. 
</P>
<P>
	More dollar weakness is putting downward pressure on U.S.  
financial markets. 
</P>
<P>
	A decline by the dollar against the Japanese yen and the euro  
are sending bond market interest rates higher. 
</P>
<P>
	And it's likely to prevent Wall Street from adding to  
yesterday's gains. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks were higher yesterday following four straight days of  
losses. 
</P>
<P>
	Another reason for hesitation in the market is tomorrow's big  
economic report. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts say many investors are standing by ahead of the key  
August employment report. 
</P>
<P>
	At the same time, the upcoming Labor Day weekend is also sapping  
investor interest. 
  	   	
