<HEADLINE> Spanish Soap Opera Star Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Fernando Carrillo, a star of Spanish soap operas,  
says he's hoping to be quickly acquitted of misdemeanor drug 
charges. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think this will jeopardize my career, because I'm  
innocent,'' Carrillo said Thursday to crowd of largely 
Spanish-language press. ``We all make mistakes. This has been a 
hold on my career for two days. I want to get it over with.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Carrillo, 33, was arrested Tuesday on marijuana and drug  
paraphernalia possession charges. Police say they found bags of 
marijuana in the Jeep driven by Carrillo's brother after it was 
pulled over for allegedly speeding through a school zone. An 
officer searched the vehicle after smelling marijuana, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police say a bag of marijuana was found where Carrillo had been  
sitting. Three additional bags were found under the seat, and a 
backpack containing a metal pipe with marijuana residue was also 
recovered, they said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Venezuelan actor said the incident has embarrassed him, but  
said he has received support from fans. 
</P>
<P>
	``The people don't want to believe what has happened,'' he said.  
``They've been giving me a lot of love in the street, which I never 
felt before.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Carrillo recently starred in the soap ``Rosalinda'' with Mexican  
actress and singer Thalia. He was arrested in Miami Beach, where he 
is to begin work on a new album, said Angela Rodriguez, his 
publicist. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
