<HEADLINE> Sterling Heights Wins at Del Mar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Sterling Heights took the lead in the  
final 100 yards and went on to win Thursday's $76,450 feature race 
at Del Mar by 3 1/2 lengths over Andoya. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Garrett Gomez and carrying 115 pounds, Sterling  
Heights covered 1 3/4 miles on turf in 2:14 4-5 and paid $27.20, 
$11.40 and $6.40. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the fourth in 16 lifetime starts for Sterling  
Heights and was worth $45,850, increasing the career earnings of 
the 4-year-old daughter of Royal Academy to $156,362. 
</P>
<P>
	Andoya, ridden by Chris McCarron and carrying 115 pounds,  
crossed the finish line a nose in front of Celibataire and returned 
$10 and $5.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Celibataire, ridden by Kent Desormeaux and carrying 114 pounds,  
was one length ahead of 2-1 favorite Cali at the wire and paid $4 
to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Following Cali across the finish line in the race for fillies  
and mares were Delivery, Kris Is It, Society Dream and Riboletta. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
