<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Buffalo's Smith To Miss Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORCHARD PARK, N.Y. (AP) -- Bruce Smith will miss Buffalo's final  
exhibition game to be with his sick father, the veteran defensive 
end said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith has decided not to play Saturday against Pittsburgh, and  
instead will spend the weekend with his father, George, in the 
family's hometown of Norfolk, Va. 
</P>
<P>
	``My father is a very sick man,'' Smith said. ``His condition is  
very serious.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith plans to return next week to prepare for the regular  
season opener at Indianapolis on Sept. 12. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'll be back in time to start preparing for the Colts,'' Smith  
said. ``But the most important thing is me having piece of mind 
where my father is concerned. God forbid something were to happen 
and I didn't take his illness seriously enough and never saw him 
again. I just can't take that chance, no matter what the cost.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith's 79-year-old father has been plagued for years by  
emphysema and heart problems, among other ailments. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a combination of a lot of things,'' said Smith, who added  
that his father cannot speak much or take more than a few steps 
without becoming exhausted. ``Emphysema for the most part.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 36-year-old Smith has battled injury and struggled through  
contract hassles in his career. ``I see now where I get the will to 
continue striving through all kinds of adversity,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith is one of the most dominant defensive players in the  
history of the game and has been selected to the Pro Bowl 11 times. 
He trails only Reggie White in career sacks. 
</P>
<P>
	Marcellus Wiley will start in Smith's place.  
</P>
<P>
	The Bills also will sit offensive lineman Joe Panos on Saturday.  
Panos was examined Thursday following a series of neck stingers. 
</P>
<P>
	Recently demoted center Dusty Zeigler will take over for Panos  
at right guard. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
