<HEADLINE> Murdoch Gives $10 Mil. to Cathedral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Rupert Murdoch on Thursday donated $10  
million to help complete construction of the $163 million Cathedral 
of Our Lady of the Angels. 
</P>
<P>
	The money will be used to build a conference center that will  
adjoin the cathedral, according to Cardinal Roger Mahony. 
</P>
<P>
	``Cardinal Mahony's vision for this beautiful new cathedral and  
all that goes with it deserves everybody's support,'' said Murdoch, 
who is not Catholic. ``It will serve the people of Southern 
California as a whole.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Murdoch is chairman of News Corp., a worldwide media  
conglomerate that includes newspapers, the Fox television network, 
20th Century Fox film studio and satellite networks in Europe and 
Asia. Through Fox Sports, he also owns the Los Angeles Dodgers. 
</P>
<P>
	The 3,000-seat Cathedral of Our Lady of the Angels is scheduled  
to open about mid-2001 in downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	When finished, the cathedral complex will include a landscaped  
plaza, meditation garden, conference center, and a 
24,000-square-foot residence for Mahony, resident clergy and 
visitors. 
</P>
<P>
	The cathedral will replace tiny St. Vibiana's Cathedral, which  
was damaged by the 1994 Northridge quake and closed. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Murdochs have long recognized the importance of Los  
Angeles as a key city for the new century and millennium, and they 
are demonstrating in a significant fashion their commitment to 
providing this world-class city with a world-class cathedral and 
conference center,'' Mahony said. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
