<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Thunderstorms dampened parts of the Gulf Coast and West on  
Thursday, while Tropical Storm Dennis churned wind and rain as it 
stayed parked off the coast of North Carolina. 
</P>
<P>
	Dennis sent light showers into Virginia and North Carolina.  
Heavier precipitation came from a disturbance along the Gulf Coast 
and lower Mississippi Valley, creating rain from Alabama into Texas 
and Oklahoma and intense thunderstorms in southern Louisiana, 
Mississippi and Alabama. 
</P>
<P>
	Showers and thundershowers were widespread from Minnesota south  
and west into Montana, Wyoming, Utah and Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
	The rest of the West, from Washington down to California, was  
fair and dry. Similar conditions prevailed from the Great Lakes and 
Northeast south into the Ohio and Tennessee valleys, because of 
high pressure over New England. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures in the Lower 48 ranged from a midday high of 95 in  
Little Rock, Ark., to a morning low of 27 in Stanley, Ore. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
