<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Diana's Mother Wnats Privacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Princess Diana's mother said on Thursday she would  
never to share her memories of her daughter with the media. 
</P>
<P>
	Frances Shand Kydd told the Daily Telegraph that hounding by the  
media as Tuesday's anniversary of Diana's death approached forced 
her out of her home in Scotland. 
</P>
<P>
	In a letter to the editor, Mrs. Shand Kydd said the dogged  
attempts by the media to get her to share her memories of Diana 
will fail. 
</P>
<P>
	``For me personally, it's draining and difficult to be regarded  
as a commercial asset -- as a boost for television audiences, 
circulations and sales promotions,'' she wrote. 
</P>
<P>
	``I shared her, not always joyfully, with the world when she was  
alive. I'm possessive, since her death, of her and of what I see to 
be the interests of her `blood' family.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
