<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Lower; Gold Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mostly lower against other  
major currencies in European trading Thursday. Gold prices were 
mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0676, up from $1.0600 Wednesday.  
Later, in midday trading in New York, the euro traded at $1.0691. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Wednesday: 109.08 Japanese  
yen, down from 109.33; 1.4955 Swiss francs, down from 1.5090; 
1.4927 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4899. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6077, up from $1.6066 late  
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 109.20 yen, and  
the pound was worth $1.6090. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth: $1.8320 German marks, down from 1.8451. 
$6.1442 French francs, down from 6.1883; 2.0642 Dutch guilders, 
down from 2.0790; and 1,813.67 Italian lire, down from 1,826.67. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold in London closed at $254.50 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$254.25 on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $254.65, up from $254.45.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $2 in Hong Kong to close at $253.85.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.16 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.17. 
  	   	
</P>
