<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Minn. Doctor Admits Ramp Assault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	APPLE VALLEY, Minn. (AP) -- A doctor pleaded guilty Thursday to  
assault charges for running a 69-year-old woman off the road, then 
hitting her, because she cut him off on a highway. 
</P>
<P>
	A lawyer for Thomas J. Valente entered the guilty plea for his  
client. Sentencing was set for next month. 
</P>
<P>
	``I confronted and struck an elderly woman, which was an  
unthinkable act,'' Valente, 41, said in a statement entered into 
the court record. 
</P>
<P>
	He said he is getting counseling for ``an acute anger management  
problem.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Virginia Hendrickson said Valente used his BMW to force her off  
a ramp, then swore at her and hit her in the face. 
</P>
<P>
	Valente, an anesthesiologist with an office in Minneapolis,  
faces a maximum penalty of 90 days in jail and a $700 fine. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
