<HEADLINE> Patriots' Take ASU's Cherry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- J'Juan Cherry, a cornerback from Arizona State,  
was chosen by the New England Patriots in an NFL supplemental draft 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Cherry, who was dropped from the Arizona State team last summer  
for violating team rules, was taken in the fourth round, meaning 
the Patriots will forfeit their fourth-round pick in next year's 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
	The only other player in the draft, defensive back Dennison  
Robinson of West Georgia, was not taken. 
  	   	
</P>
