<HEADLINE> Bruins Sign Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Two Boston Bruins players who spent most of last  
season in the AHL and a goalie who spent the entire season in the 
minor league agreed to contracts with the NHL team. 
</P>
<P>
	Left wing Antti Laaksonen and goalie John Grahame agreed to  
one-year contracts and defenseman Mattias Timander agreed to a 
two-year deal. 
</P>
<P>
	Laaksonen, 25, had one goal in 11 games with Boston and 25 goals  
in 66 games with its minor-league affiliate in Providence last 
season. Timander, 25, had no goals and six assists in 22 games with 
Boston and two goals and 22 assists with Providence. 
</P>
<P>
	Graham, who spent the last two seasons at Providence after  
playing for Lake Superior State, had a 2.90 goals against average 
and 37-9-1 record for the team that won the AHL championship. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
